Name: product_version_id
Description: The product_version_id attribute identifies the version of an individual data product.

Name: mapping_cycle
Description: The mapping cycle in which the data were acquired. Should be 1 to 6.

Name: orbit_number
Description: The orbit_number attribute identifies the number of the orbital revolution around a target body.

Name: start_orbit_number
Description: Provides the the lowest revolution orbit number that contributed data to a given data product.

Name: stop_orbit_number
Description: Provides the the highest revolution orbit number that contributed data to a given data product.

Name: mission_phase_name
Description: The mission_phase_name attribute provides the mission-defined name of a time period within the mission.

Name: Aerobraking
Description: The aerobraking phase extended from completion of the fourth mapping cycle through achievement of a near-circular orbit. Circularization was achieved more quickly than expected; the first gravity data collection in the circular orbit was not scheduled until 11 days later. Orbits included within the aerobraking phase were 7627 through 8392. Started 1993-05-26 and ended on 1993-08-05.

Name: Mapping Cycle 1
Description: The first mapping cycle extended from completion of the orbit trim and checkout phase until completion of one cycle of radar mapping (approximately 243 days). Started 1990-09-15 and ended 1991-05-15.

Name: Mapping Cycle 2
Description: The second mapping cycle extended from completion of the first mapping cycle through an additional cycle of mapping. Acquisition of 'right-looking' SAR data was emphasized. Radio occultation measurements were carried out on orbits 3212-3214. A period of battery reconditioning followed completion of Cycle 2. Started 1991-05-16 and ended 1992-01-17.

Name: Mapping Cycle 3
Description: The third mapping cycle extended from completion of battery reconditioning through an additional cycle of mapping (approximately 243 days). Acquisition of 'stereo' SAR data was emphasized. The last orbit in the third cycle was orbit 5747. Started 1992-01-24 and ended 1992-09-14.

Name: Mapping Cycle 4
Description: The fourth mapping cycle extended from completion of the third mapping cycle through an additional cycle of mapping. Acquisition of radio tracking data for gravity studies was emphasized. Radio occultation measurements were carried out on orbits 6369, 6370, 6471, and 6472. Because of poor observing geometry for gravity data collection at the beginning of the cycle, this cycle was extended 10 days beyond the nominal 243 days. Orbits included within the fourth cycle were 5748 through 7626. Periapsis was lowered on orbit 5752 to improve sensitivity to gravity features in Cycle 4. Started 1992-09-14 and ended 1993-05-25.

Name: Mapping Cycle 5
Description: The fifth mapping cycle extended from completion of the aerobraking phase through an additional cycle of mapping (approximately 243 days). Acquisition of radio tracking data for gravity studies was emphasized. The first orbit in the fifth cycle was orbit 8393. Started on 1993-08-16 and ended on 1994-04-15.

Name: Mapping Cycle 6
Description: The sixth mapping cycle extended from completion of the fifth mapping cycle through an additional cycle of mapping (approximately 243 days). Acquisition of radio tracking data for gravity studies was emphasized. The first orbit in the sixth cycle was orbit 12249. Started on 1994-04-16.

Name: Primary Mission
Description: The prime science phase of the mission. This value occurs in the original PDS labels of the MIDR products.

Name: radar_look_direction
Description: The radar_look_direction attribute provides the direction the radar antenna was pointing relative to the spacecraft ground track along a given orbit. Most cases were Left or Right. Stereo indicates left looking with an incidence angle for stereo measurements. Maxwell is a special case for observing the Maxwell feature.

Name: Left
Description: Left looking observation

Name: Maxwell
Description: Maxwell observation

Name: Mixed
Description: Mixed looking observation (both left and right)

Name: Right
Description: Right looking observation

Name: Stereo
Description: Stereo observation

Name: spacecraft_clock_count_partition
Description: The spacecraft_clock_count_partition attribute indicates the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start_count and spacecraft_clock_stop_count attributes.

Name: spacecraft_clock_start_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

Name: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of a time period of interest.

Name: band_name
Description: The name of the radio band in which the signal was received.

Name: S
Description: S band

Name: X
Description: X band

Description: The radio polarization of the receiving antenna and feed.

Name: left circular
Description: Left circular polarization

Name: right circular
Description: Right circular polarization

Name: dsn_station_number
Description: The number of the DSN antenna used to collect the data.

Name: organization_id
Description: The organization that produced the data.

Name: SUE
Description: Stanford University Element of the Venus Express Radio Science Team

Name: producer_institution_name
Description: The producer_institution_name attribute identifies a university, research center, NASA center, or other institution associated with the production of a data product.

Description: The original PDS volume_id of where the Magellan data are located.
